#################################################################
#                          WARNING!!!!                          #
#                                                               #
# THE AUTO INSTALLER CREATES PARTITIONS ON THE DESTINATION DISK #
# ERASING THE PREVIOUS CONTENTS: YOU'LL LOST ALL YOUR DATA ON   #
# DESTINATION DISK, SO BE CAREFUL BEFORE USING THIS TOOL!!!!    #
#################################################################	

INFO:
-----

Slack-Kickstart provides automatic installation of Slackware and Slackware64 
Linux distribution.

REQUIREMENTS:
-------------

- A kernel with loopback device support (Slackware standard kernel is OK).
- Tcl & Tk (Needed to run the configuration GUI TkGui.tcl).
- syslinux (Needed to create Iso & PXE images).
- cdrtools (as above).
- openssl (Needed to encrypt the root password).

QUICKSTART:
-----------

You need to download some kernels into kernels subdir.
You can use original Slackware, or Slackware64, kernels, or any
custom kernel, but if you choose the 'custom' 
way you need built-in support for ethernet card and
system disks device.

Kernel images can be stored in any directory layout:

kernels-\
	|
	[dir] bare.i
    	|	\
	|	bzImage		
	|
	[dir] scsi.s 
    	|	\
	|	bzImage		
	|
	[dir] adaptec.s 
    	|	\
	|	bzImage		
	|
	[dir] custom
	|	\
	|	mykernel1 mykernel2 ...	
	

See the online tutorial at:

 http://www.slack-kickstart.org/index.php?ART=documentation

CONFIG FILE:
------------

~~~ SNIP ~~~
DISTRO=slackware64-13.37
# Hostname to use, however this gets over-riden by hostname from DHCP server
HOSTNAME=slack-kickstart
ETH=eth0
PACKAGE_SERVER=nfs:10.117.8.1:/mnt/linux_install/slackware/slackware64-13.37
TAG=s64-13.37-light
# Root password
PASSWD=password
KERNEL=kernels/huge.s/bzImage
# Type of auto-update: slapt-get, swaret, slackpkg
AUTOUPDATE=none
# If true, only SSHd should be started after installation
SECURE=yes

# Dynamic IP settings from DHCP
DHCP=yes

# Static IP settings - these are mutually exclusive with DHCP=yes
INET=1.2.3.4
MASK=255.255.255.0
GW=1.2.3.5
NS1=1.2.3.6
NS2=1.2.3.7
# END static IP settings

# Auto-start installation
AUTOSTART=no

SLAPTGET=http://software.jaos.org/slackpacks/10.2/slapt-get-0.9.11a-i386-1.tgz
NTPHOST=ntp.server.net
# Where individual config per host can be downloaded. http:// is presumed.
CONFIGHOST=10.117.8.2
# List of post-installation scripts to execute
POSTINST="ssh.sh,sysctl.sh"

# Partition scheme.
# % sfdisk; format is used to define partitions
DISK="DEVICE[/dev/vda]=[/],[ext4],[,2750,83];[swap],[swap],[,250,82];"

# Timezone, Keymap & HWClock
KEYMAP=qwerty/us.map
HWCLOCK=utc
TIMEZONE=Europe/Prague
~~~ SNIP ~~~

